abstract.text: The details about a call handled by your app.

inlineContent.text: object stores details about calls made by the user through your app. You use call record objects to communicate basic information about calls to SiriKit. A call record identifies the type of call, the duration of the call, the date and time of the call, and the person on the other end of the call. You create call record objects when reporting search results back to SiriKit and when identifying voicemails to play.
